Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Thinly slice the @portobello mushrooms{2}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%grams} and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the saucepan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high
heat. Once hot, add the @British chicken breast{240%grams}(diced) and cook until
browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Put the frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil (if needed) and
fry the portobello and @sliced mushrooms{120%grams} until browned, stirring
occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Lower the heat to medium and add the onion. Cook, stirring frequently, until
softened, ~{6-8%minutes}. Add the garlic and @balsamic vinegar{12%milliliter} and
cook until evaporated, ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

When the veg is cooked, stir in the browned chicken, @UHT cooking cream{150%grams},
@vegetable stock paste{10%grams} and the @water{100%milliliter}(for the sauce).

Bring to the boil and simmer, stirring occasionally, until reduced, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the chicken.

Once the sauce is reduced, stir through the cooked penne and @hard Italian style
cheese{40%grams}(grated) until piping hot and melted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of
water if it's a little thick.

Share your chicken and double mushroom penne between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!